iaik.security.cipher

Class RC5KeyGenerator

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.crypto.KeyGeneratorSpi
      • iaik.security.cipher.VarLengthKeyGenerator
        • iaik.security.cipher.RC5KeyGenerator

  • public class RC5KeyGenerator
extends VarLengthKeyGenerator
    This class provides the functionality of KeyGenerator for generating keys to be used by the RC5 or RC6 ciphers.

    An application uses 

     KeyGenerator key_gen = KeyGenerator.getInstance("RC5");
    for creating a KeyGenerator object for the RC5 algorithm. For actually generating the requested secret key from the KeyGenerator object just created, an application calls the generateKey method after having initialized the generator with some random seed or relied on the default system-provided source of randomness: 

     SecretKey new_key = key_gen.generateKey();

    Version:
    File Revision 11
    See Also:
    KeyGenerator, KeyGeneratorSpi, SecretKey, SecretKey, RC5
